-- LVMH Names Patrice Wagner as Head of Bon Marche Department Store in Paris
-- B y   P a u l   J a r v i s
-- 2010-10-07T15:42:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/lvmh-names-patrice-wagner-as-head-of-bon-marche-department-store-in-paris.html
LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA ,
world’s largest maker of luxury goods, named  Patrice Wagner  as
head of the Bon Marche department-store in Paris.  Wagner, a former general manager of Berlin’s KaDeWe
department store, will succeed  Philippe de Beauvoir  as chairman
of Le Bon Marche Group on Oct. 12, and will also become chief
executive officer of the unit, LVMH said today in a statement.
De Beauvoir will retire on the same date.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Paul Jarvis  in London at 
 pjarvis@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 